// ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
// Prisma Schema — DecentralChain Airdrop Bot
// ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

generator client {
  provider      = "prisma-client-js"
  binaryTargets = ["native", "linux-musl-arm64-openssl-3.0.x", "linux-musl-openssl-3.0.x"]
}

datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
  url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
}

// ── User ──────────────────────────────────

model User {
  id             String    @id @default(cuid())
  telegramId     BigInt    @unique
  username       String?
  firstName      String?
  lastName       String?
  isAdmin        Boolean   @default(false)
  referralCode   String    @unique
  referredByUserId String?
  referredByUser User?     @relation("Referrals", fields: [referredByUserId], references: [id])
  referrals      User[]    @relation("Referrals")

  wallets              Wallet[]
  eligibilitySnapshots EligibilitySnapshot[]
  referralsMade        ReferralEvent[]  @relation("ReferralsMade")
  referralsReceived    ReferralEvent[]  @relation("ReferralsReceived")
  referralRewards      ReferralReward[]
  claimRecords         ClaimRecord[]
  inviteRewards        InviteReward[]
  dccPurchases         DccPurchase[]
  dccLocks             DccLock[]
  lockReferralRewards  LockReferralReward[]
  dccDeposits          DccDeposit[]
  solanaWallet         SolanaWallet?
  auditLogs            AuditLog[]       @relation("AuditActor")

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([telegramId])
  @@index([referralCode])
}

// ── Wallet ────────────────────────────────

model Wallet {
  id                            String    @id @default(cuid())
  userId                        String
  user                          User      @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  address                       String
  encryptedSeed                 String?
  isVerified                    Boolean   @default(false)
  verificationMethod            String?
  verificationChallenge         String?
  verificationChallengeExpiresAt DateTime?
  verifiedAt                    DateTime?

  eligibilitySnapshots EligibilitySnapshot[]
  claimRecords         ClaimRecord[]

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@unique([userId, address])
  @@index([address])
  @@index([userId])
}

// ── EligibilitySnapshot ───────────────────

model EligibilitySnapshot {
  id                  String   @id @default(cuid())
  userId              String
  user                User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  walletId            String
  wallet              Wallet   @relation(fields: [walletId], references: [id])
  eligible            Boolean
  stDCCBalance        BigInt   @default(0)
  poolCount           Int      @default(0)
  swapCount           Int      @default(0)
  dappCount           Int      @default(0)
  hasCurrentLp        Boolean  @default(false)
  lpAgeBlocks         Int      @default(0)
  walletAgeOk         Boolean  @default(false)
  txCountOk           Boolean  @default(false)
  sybilFlag           Boolean  @default(false)
  claimed             Boolean  @default(false)
  rawScore            Float?
  estimatedAllocation Float?
  snapshotJson        String?

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([walletId])
}

// ── ReferralEvent ─────────────────────────
// Multi-level: each event records the direct referrer → referred pair.
// The `tier` field indicates which level this referral is at:
//   tier 1 = direct referral (A invites B)
//   tier 2 = B's referee was invited because of A's chain (B invites C → A gets tier-2 credit)
//   tier 3 = (C invites D → A gets tier-3 credit)
// For a single referred user joining, multiple ReferralEvent rows may be
// created — one per ancestor up to MAX_REFERRAL_DEPTH.

model ReferralEvent {
  id              String  @id @default(cuid())
  referrerUserId  String
  referrerUser    User    @relation("ReferralsMade", fields: [referrerUserId], references: [id])
  referredUserId  String
  referredUser    User    @relation("ReferralsReceived", fields: [referredUserId], references: [id])
  code            String
  tier            Int     @default(1) // 1 = direct, 2 = second-level, 3 = third-level
  status          ReferralStatus @default(PENDING)
  metadataJson    String?

  rewards ReferralReward[]

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@unique([referrerUserId, referredUserId])
  @@index([referredUserId])
  @@index([referrerUserId])
  @@index([referrerUserId, tier])
  @@index([code])
  @@index([tier])
}

enum ReferralStatus {
  PENDING
  WALLET_CONNECTED
  WALLET_VERIFIED
  ELIGIBLE
  REWARDED
  REJECTED
}

// ── ReferralReward ────────────────────────

model ReferralReward {
  id                    String  @id @default(cuid())
  userId                String
  user                  User    @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  sourceReferralEventId String
  sourceReferralEvent   ReferralEvent @relation(fields: [sourceReferralEventId], references: [id])
  rewardType            String  @default("referral_bonus")
  tier                  Int     @default(1)
  amount                Float
  status                RewardStatus @default(PENDING)

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([tier])
}

enum RewardStatus {
  PENDING
  CREDITED
  CLAIMED
  CANCELLED
}

// ── ClaimRecord ───────────────────────────

model ClaimRecord {
  id           String      @id @default(cuid())
  userId       String
  user         User        @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  walletId     String
  wallet       Wallet      @relation(fields: [walletId], references: [id])
  campaignId   String?
  status       ClaimStatus @default(PENDING)
  txId         String?
  amount       Float?
  metadataJson String?

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([walletId])
  @@index([txId])
}

enum ClaimStatus {
  PENDING
  SUBMITTED
  CONFIRMED
  FAILED
  CANCELLED
}

// ── InviteReward ──────────────────────────
// Instant 1 DCC reward for each invited user who starts the bot.
// Separate from the tiered ReferralReward system (which requires eligibility).

model InviteReward {
  id             String   @id @default(cuid())
  userId         String                        // the inviter who earns the reward
  user           User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  invitedUserId  String                        // the person who was invited
  amount         Float    @default(1)          // DCC amount (1 per invite)
  redeemed       Boolean  @default(false)
  redeemedAt     DateTime?
  redeemTxId     String?

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())

  @@unique([userId, invitedUserId])            // one reward per invited user
  @@index([userId])
  @@index([redeemed])
}

// ── DccPurchase ───────────────────────────
// Off-chain DCC purchased via SOL/USDC/USDT through the bridge API.
// User can /redeem to move purchased DCC to their on-chain wallet.

model DccPurchase {
  id               String         @id @default(cuid())
  userId           String
  user             User           @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  token            String                    // SOL, USDC, USDT
  amountPaid       Float                     // amount in source token
  dccAmount        Float                     // DCC received/expected
  bridgeTransferId String?                   // transfer ID from bridge API
  depositAddress   String?                   // Solana deposit address
  status           PurchaseStatus @default(PENDING)
  solanaTxId       String?
  redeemed         Boolean        @default(false)
  redeemedAt       DateTime?
  redeemTxId       String?

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([status])
  @@index([userId, status])
}

enum PurchaseStatus {
  PENDING
  DEPOSITED
  COMPLETED
  FAILED
  EXPIRED
}

// ── SolanaWallet ──────────────────────────
// Custodial Solana keypair used to sign bridge transactions on behalf of the user.
// Private key is encrypted at rest using AES-256-GCM.

model SolanaWallet {
  id           String @id @default(cuid())
  userId       String @unique
  user         User   @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  publicKey    String @unique       // base58 Solana public key
  encryptedKey String               // AES-256-GCM encrypted secret key

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())

  @@index([publicKey])
}

// ── DccLock ───────────────────────────────
// Off-chain DCC locking: 3% daily rewards, 30-day lock period.
// Users can lock available off-chain DCC (min 100) and compound earnings.

model DccLock {
  id          String     @id @default(cuid())
  userId      String
  user        User       @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  amount      Float                          // DCC locked
  dailyRate   Float      @default(0.03)      // 3% per day
  startedAt   DateTime   @default(now())
  expiresAt   DateTime                       // startedAt + 30 days
  status      LockStatus @default(ACTIVE)
  earnedDcc   Float      @default(0)         // snapshot of earned at unlock
  unlockedAt  DateTime?
  earningsRedeemed   Boolean   @default(false)
  earningsRedeemedAt DateTime?
  earningsRedeemTxId String?

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([status])
}

enum LockStatus {
  ACTIVE
  COMPLETED
  WITHDRAWN
}

// ── LockReferralReward ─────────────────
// When a lock is finalized, each upline referrer (up to 3 tiers)
// receives a % of the lock's earned DCC as a referral commission.

model LockReferralReward {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  userId      String                       // the referrer who earns the commission
  user        User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  lockId      String                       // the lock that generated this reward
  lockOwnerId String                       // the user who owned the lock
  tier        Int                          // 1 = direct, 2 = second-level, 3 = third
  rate        Float                        // commission rate applied (e.g. 0.10)
  amount      Float                        // DCC credited
  redeemed    Boolean  @default(false)
  redeemedAt  DateTime?
  redeemTxId  String?

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())

  @@unique([userId, lockId])               // one reward per referrer per lock
  @@index([userId])
  @@index([lockId])
}

// ── DccDeposit ────────────────────────────
// On-chain DCC sent to the rewards wallet gets credited to off-chain balance.
// txId is unique to prevent double-credit.

model DccDeposit {
  id            String   @id @default(cuid())
  userId        String
  user          User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
  txId          String   @unique              // on-chain transfer tx ID
  amount        Float                         // DCC credited
  senderAddress String                        // user's wallet address
  status        String   @default("COMPLETED")

  createdAt DateTime @default(now())

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([txId])
}

// ── CampaignConfig ────────────────────────

model CampaignConfig {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  key       String   @unique
  valueJson String
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt
}

// ── AuditLog ──────────────────────────────

model AuditLog {
  id           String   @id @default(cuid())
  actorType    String   // "user" | "admin" | "system" | "bot"
  actorId      String?
  actor        User?    @relation("AuditActor", fields: [actorId], references: [id])
  action       String
  targetType   String?  // "user" | "wallet" | "referral" | "claim"
  targetId     String?
  metadataJson String?
  createdAt    DateTime @default(now())

  @@index([actorId])
  @@index([action])
  @@index([createdAt])
}
